<subSubSection id="C341A8F90132A941FE05AB17FCA9FD25" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE4FB720132A941FE05AB17FCA9FD25" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,2027]" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">
—This species was only mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA86830132A941FC44AB17FBCDFE5F" box="[954,1105,367,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" refId="ref8828" refString="Jaksic, P. (1988) Privremene karte rasprostranjenosti dnevnih leptira Jugoslavije (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). Jugoslavensko entomolosko drustvo, Posebna izdanja, Zagreb, 214 pp." type="book">Jakšić (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and Švara 
<emphasis id="B92F27600132A941FB2CAB09FA97FE5F" box="[1234,1291,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">et al.</emphasis>
(2015) from 
<collectingRegion id="499F35900132A941FF69ABECFF79FE7A" box="[151,229,404,429]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">Skadar</collectingRegion>
Lake. It is widespread along much of the northern side of the lake where its host plant 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B80F10132A941FB52ABECFA81FE7A" box="[1196,1309,404,429]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Polycitoridae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis id="B92F27600132A941FB52ABECFA81FE7A" box="[1196,1309,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">Salix alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.grows in abundance (Franeta pers. obs.). Compared to its European distribution (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA86830132A941FC17ABCFFB5EFE07" box="[1001,1218,439,464]" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" refId="ref9940" refString="Masui, A., Bozano, G. C. &amp; Floriani, A. (2011) Guide to the Butterflies of the Palearctic region. Nymphalidae, subfamily Apaturinae. Part IV. Omnes Artes S. A. S., Milano, 82 pp." type="book">
Masui 
<emphasis id="B92F27600132A941FBC3ABC1FBE7FE07" box="[1085,1147,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
), the 
<collectingRegion id="499F35900132A941FAF4ABCFFAC4FE07" box="[1290,1368,439,464]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">Skadar</collectingRegion>
Lake population is very isolated, almost 
<quantity id="4CA356970132A941FDE2ABA4FDF6FE22" box="[540,618,476,501]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" unit="km" value="300.0">300km</quantity>
from the nearest Greek populations and about the same distance from the closest Serbian colonies (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA86830132A941FE4AAB87FDFDFDCF" box="[436,609,511,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" refId="ref10255" refString="Pamperis, L. (2009) Butterflies of Greece (Second edition). Pamperis, Athens, 766 pp." type="book">Pamperis 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA86830132A941FD93AB87FC13FDCF" box="[621,911,511,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" refId="ref10074" refString="Miljevic, M. &amp; Popovic, M. (2014) Alciphron-Database of insects of Serbia: Lepidoptera, Papilionoidea. HabiProt, Belgrade. Available from: http: // alciphron. habiprot. org. rs (accessed 7 January 2018)" type="journal article">Miljević &amp; Popović 2014</bibRefCitation>
), and for some time there was doubt regarding its occurrence in this region. The species has recently been observed on the Albanian shores of the 
<collectingRegion id="499F35900132A941FAF3A85CFAC7FDEA" box="[1293,1371,548,573]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">Skadar</collectingRegion>
Lake (Micevski 
<emphasis id="B92F27600132A941FEECA831FED8FDB7" box="[274,324,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">et al</emphasis>
. 2015). The presence of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5B80F10132A941FD97A830FD59FDB7" authorityName="Freyer" authorityYear="1829" box="[617,709,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Apatura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metis">
<emphasis id="B92F27600132A941FD97A830FD59FDB7" box="[617,709,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">A. metis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F34CBBE20132A941FD10A830FCEBFDB7" box="[750,887,584,608]" name="Serbia" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
might be overlooked by its unusual phenology, compared to other populations from the rest of its European range (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCA86830132A941FC75A814FBC9FD53" box="[907,1109,620,645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="141" refId="ref9940" refString="Masui, A., Bozano, G. C. &amp; Floriani, A. (2011) Guide to the Butterflies of the Palearctic region. Nymphalidae, subfamily Apaturinae. Part IV. Omnes Artes S. A. S., Milano, 82 pp." type="book">
Masui 
<emphasis id="B92F27600132A941FC24A815FB8FFD52" box="[986,1043,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). It usually starts to fly at the end of June and continues until the second half of July, with a peak flight period in the first week of July (Franeta pers. obs.). The number of generations at the 
<collectingRegion id="499F35900132A941FD5EA8CCFD72FD1A" box="[672,750,692,717]" country="Albania" name="Shkoder" pageId="13" pageNumber="141">Skadar</collectingRegion>
Lake colony is yet to be determined and it is quite possible that another (2nd) generation might occur later in the season.
</paragraph>
